---+++ Interesting/Various
   * Manfred S.and Sauermann A.,&#8221;Linearization of arguments in commentary text,&#8221; in Multidisciplinary Approaches to Discourse 2008 - MAD 08,20-23 February 2008, Lysebu, Oslo, 2008
   * [[http://www.igi-global.com/article/from-argument-diagrams-to-argumentation-mining-in-texts/87173][From Argument Diagrams to Argumentation Mining in Texts: A Survey]]
   * Kirschner P.A.,Shum S.J.B.,and Carr C.S.,Visualizing argumentation:software tools for collaborative and educational sensemaking.:Springer-Verlag,2003.
   * How Argumentation can Enhance Dialogues in Social Networks http://www.inf.kcl.ac.uk/staff/mcburney/downloads/pubs/2010/pm-2010-10.pdf 
   * Identifying High-Level Organizational Elements in Argumentative Discourse http://aclweb.org/anthology/N/N12/N12-1003.pdf
      * Detect shell phrases
   * %X% Artem Vovk's work
   * %X% [[http://gdac.uqam.ca/proceedingEDM2008.pdf#page=202][Argument mining using highly structured argument repertoire]]
      * *very similar research vision* MUST READ!

---+++ Corpus Creation
   * Ranking the annotators: An agreement study on argumentation structure (Peldszus & Stede, 2013) 7th Ling. Annot. Workshop, ACL2013
      * http://aclweb.org/anthology//W/W13/W13-2324.pdf
      * All-annotators agreement evaluated on the scale of Landis and Koch, 1977
      * Krippendorff 1980: category definition test (one vs. all categories); category distinction test (collapse two categories)
      * Further Reading:
         * Geertzen and Bund 2006:  Measuring annotator agreement in a complex hierarchical dialogue act annotation scheme. In Proceedings of the 7th SIGdial Workshop on Discourse and Dialogue, SigDIAL 06, pages 126133, Stroudsburg,PA, USA. Association for Computational Linguistics
         * Krippendorff (1980): Content Analysis: An Introduction to its Methodology. Sage Publications, Beverly Hills, CA

   * An inter-annotator measurement methodology for the Turkish Discourse Treebank (TDB) (&#350;aban &#304; Hsan Yalcinkaya, 2010)
      * http://etd.lib.metu.edu.tr/upload/12612643/index.pdf
      * re-read
      * %X% presents a thorough study of IAA measures for discourse tasks

   * Inter-coder agreement for computational linguistics (Artstein, R., & Poesio, M., 2008)
      * overview paper
      * %X% as a reference, why Krippendorff's unitized alpha is best suitable for arbitrary spans

   * Annotating opinions in the world press, Wilson and Wiebe 2003
      * http://people.cs.pitt.edu/~wiebe/pubs/papers/sigdial03FixedLater.pdf
      * %X% source of one of the applied IAA metrics

   * On the Reliability of Unitizing Continuous Data (Krippendorf, 1995)
      * also: Measuring the Reliability of Qualitative Text Analysis Data (Krippendorff, 2004)
      * %X% source of one of the applied IAA metrics

   * Jacob Cohen. A coefficient of agreement for nominal scales. Educational and Psychological Measurement, 20(1):3746, 1960. http://www.psych.umn.edu/faculty/waller/classes/meas11/Readings/Cohen1960.pdf (NotInBib)

   * J.R. Landis and G.G. Koch. The measurement of observer agreement for categorical data. Biometrics, 32(1):159174, March 1977 (NotInBib)
      * Evaluation scale for kappa


