---+++ Legal Argumentation
   * [[http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1568246][Argumentation mining: the detection, classification and structure of arguments in text]]
      * %X% standard citation - "inventors" of term AM
   * Argumentation mining (2011) http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10506-010-9104-x/fulltext.html
   * Automatic Detection and Classification Argumentation in a Legal Case (Mochales, 2011) 
      * also: Identifying arguments in legal texts (ACILA project) http://www.arg.dundee.ac.uk/people/chris/publications/2007/icail2007.pdf
   * Towards Automated Identification and Analysis of Argumentation Structures in the Decision Corpus of the German Federal Constitutionals Court (Huoy et al., 2013) 7th IEEE Int. Conf. on Digital Ecosystems and Technologies (DEST), 2013
      * context of ARGUMENTUM
   * ARGUMENTUM - Towards Computer-Supported Analysis, Retrieval and Synthesis of Argumentation Structures in Humanities Using the Example of Jurisprudence http://dfki.de/KI2012/PosterDemoTrack/ki2012pd07.pdf
   * On the extraction of decisions and contributions from summaries of French legal IT contract cases http://lexitron.nectec.or.th/public/LREC-2010_Malta/workshops/W23.pdf#page=35
   * Argumentation structures in legal dossiers http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=1276318.1276371


